verbs.description: distend (third-person singular simple present distends, present participle distending, simple past and past participle distended)

entries.meaning: (intransitive) To extend or expand, as from internal pressure; to swell
(transitive, reflexive, archaic) To extend; to stretch out; to spread out.
examples: I begin to hate the theater, the feeling wickedly distended by histrionics, all my old gestures, clutchings, tears, and applications. These impure and frail matters are conteined within the angust concave of the Lunar Orb, above which with uninterrupted Series the things Celestial distend themselves.
